title: Curriculum vitae
---
body:

My (professional) life, in bullet points:
* Born in Belfeld, a village near Maastricht in the Netherlands.
* Studied [Applied Mathematics](http://www.math.utwente.nl) and [Computer Science](http://www.cs.utwente.nl) at the [University of Twente](http://www.utwente.nl) in Enschede, the Netherlands.
* PhD student of [Arieh Iserles](http://www.damtp.cam.ac.uk/user/na/people/Arieh/) at the [Numerical Analysis](http://www.damtp.cam.ac.uk/user/na/na.html) group of the [Department of Applied Mathematics and Theoretical Physics](http://www.amtp.cam.ac.uk/) at the [University of Cambridge](http://www.cam.ac.uk).
* Two-month stint at the [International University Bremen](http://www.iu-bremen.de/index.html) in Germany
* Postdoc for 2&frac12; years at the [Mathematics Department](http://www.ma.hw.ac.uk/maths.html) of [Heriot-Watt University](http://www.hw.ac.uk), Edinburgh
* Postdoc for 1&frac12; years at the [Mathematics Section](http://www.latrobe.edu.au/mathstats/maths/index.html) of [La Trobe University](http://www.latrobe.edu.au) in Melbourne.
* Moved to Leeds in October 2007 and stayed there until now as a lecturer in the
Department of Applied Mathematics.

More information can be found in the formal curriculum vitae, which is available in [PDF format](cv.pdf).
